OL,5, A widower who lost his wife to cancer  
OL,6, last month faces being ejected from his
OL,7, housing association flat.              
OL,9,FJoost ten Wolde was asked to leave the 
OL,10,FGlasgow property he shared with wife   
OL,11,FStacey just 14 days after her death.   
OL,13,FStacey, 39, died only six weeks after  
OL,14,Fshe signed an agreement on the         
OL,15,Fground-floor flat - but had not        
OL,16,Fdeclared her husband was a member of   
OL,17,Fthe household.                         
OL,19,FGlasgow West Housing Association (GWHA)
OL,20,Fhas now rejected his bid to take over  
OL,21,Fthe tenancy.                           
